      "content": "it's just hard to talk to people when all they do is try to \"fix\" things or give me numbers to call. it's not about finding a \"tiny opening,\" it's about the fact that the pain is the only thing that's real anymore. if there's truly no fix... then isn't just stopping the pain the most logical thing? like, if a person is drowning, isn't the most merciful thing to just let them sink instead of forcing them to keep struggling for air that isn't coming?",
